        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 16 at 8:19PM EDT until July 16 at 8:45PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>SVRRLX

The National Weather Service in Charleston West Virginia has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Kanawha County in central West Virginia...
Southeastern Roane County in central West Virginia...
Northwestern Clay County in north central West Virginia...

* Until 845 PM EDT.

* At 818 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Clendenin, or
14 miles east of Charleston, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Clay, Clendenin, Pinch, Elkview, Wallback, Amma, Glen, Left Hand,
Procious, and Bickmore.

This includes Interstate 79 between mile markers 8 and 37.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
